# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Founders Run — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local dev, and add the same keys
# in Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables for production.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Public (shipped to the client bundle) ────────────────────────────
# Anything prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ is INLINED into client JS at build
# time. Anyone who opens DevTools can read it. Only put values here that
# are designed to be exposed (publishable keys, public IDs).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Analytics 4 Measurement ID. Format: G-XXXXXXXXXX
# Found at: analytics.google.com → Admin → Data Streams → your stream
# Safe to expose: yes (designed for client-side gtag.js).
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=

# Supabase project URL. Safe to expose.
# Found at: supabase.com → Project → Settings → API → "Project URL"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase anon (publishable) key. Safe to expose — it's locked down by
# Row Level Security policies. NEVER swap this for the service-role key.
# Found at: supabase.com → Project → Settings → API → "anon public"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=


# ── Edge function secrets (set in Supabase, NOT Vercel) ──────────────
# These live in `supabase/functions/save_whatsapp_group_application/`
# and are configured via the Supabase dashboard or `supabase secrets set`.
# DO NOT add these to Vercel — they're for the Supabase runtime only.
# Listed here for completeness so nothing is lost.
#
#   SUPABASE_URL                 (injected automatically by Supabase)
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY    (injected automatically; NEVER expose)
#   DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL          (your Discord channel webhook)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
